        "label": "Workflow Documentation",
        "nodeType": "graph_note",
        "properties": {
          "title": "Dual Consciousness Mode v3.0 - Iterative Refinement Graph",
          "content": "PURPOSE: This graph implements iterative refinement with feedback loops to prevent hallucinations and ensure quality responses.\n\nFLOW OVERVIEW:\n1. User Input → Orchestrator LLM (analyzes intent, determines routing)\n2. Memory Router → Search Interpreter (evaluates relevance, signals 'unknownSignal' if no relevant memories)\n3. Context Builder (combines memories + unknownSignal into context package)\n4. Response Synthesizer (generates response using persona + context)\n5. Quality Scorer (evaluates response quality, detects hallucinations)\n6. Safety Validator (checks for policy violations)\n7. Feedback Router (CRITICAL: decides output vs loop back)\n   - If quality/safety PASS → routes to Stream Writer (output)\n   - If FAIL → routes feedbackContext back to Orchestrator (iteration)\n8. Max 3 iterations to prevent infinite loops\n\nKEY INNOVATION: Search Interpreter\n- Evaluates if memory search results actually answer the user's question\n- Sets 'unknownSignal=true' if no relevant memories found\n- Prevents hallucination by telling persona to say 'I don't know'\n\nBACK-EDGE: Link 131 connects Feedback Router → Orchestrator for iterative refinement.\n\nNODE IDS:\n- 1: User Input | 24: Orchestrator | 6: Memory Router | 32: Search Interpreter\n- 8: Context Builder | 17: Response Synthesizer | 33: Quality Scorer\n- 19: Safety Validator | 20: Response Refiner | 34: Feedback Router\n- 23: Stream Writer | 31: Thinking Stripper | 21: Memory Capture",
          "style": "info"
        },
        "comment": "Documentation node explaining the iterative refinement architecture"
      },
      "width": 600,
      "height": 350
    }
  ],
